The paper deals with target detection in hyperspectral imagery, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV). The methods presented involve machine learning techniques, specifically concept learning and discriminative modeling, which are core topics in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the use of mixed and imprecisely-labeled data, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR) and neural networks (NE).
